**banner.ts provides terminal output formatting for the ARE installer via ASCII art rendering, help text generation, and styled console messages using picocolors.**

## Exported Functions

**displayBanner()** renders ASCII art "ARE" logo in green via `pc.green()` with version string from `VERSION` constant and tagline "AI-friendly codebase documentation".

**showHelp()** outputs usage documentation including runtime flags (`--runtime claude|opencode|gemini|all`), location flags (`-g|--global`, `-l|--local`), operational flags (`-u|--uninstall`, `--force`, `-q|--quiet`), and example invocations with descriptions.

**showSuccess(msg: string)** prefixes message with green checkmark `✓` via `pc.green()`.

**showError(msg: string)** prefixes message with red X `✗` via `pc.red()`.

**showWarning(msg: string)** prefixes message with yellow exclamation `!` via `pc.yellow()`.

**showInfo(msg: string)** prefixes message with cyan arrow `>` via `pc.cyan()`.

**showNextSteps(runtime: string, filesCreated: number)** displays post-install instructions listing seven ARE commands (`/are-help`, `/are-init`, `/are-discover`, `/are-generate`, `/are-update`, `/are-specify`, `/are-clean`) with GitHub documentation link.

## Exported Constants

**VERSION** contains package version extracted via `getVersion()` from `../../package.json` using `fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)` for ESM path resolution, falls back to `'unknown'` on read failure.

## Dependencies

Imports `readFileSync` from `fs`, `dirname`/`join` from `path`, `fileURLToPath` from `url`, and default export `pc` from `picocolors` for terminal color codes.

## Design Pattern

Uses picocolors functional color API (`pc.green()`, `pc.red()`, `pc.yellow()`, `pc.cyan()`, `pc.dim()`, `pc.bold()`) for ANSI escape code generation without chaining methods, enabling conditional color application based on TTY detection.